column5: Flyin into Duluth while the rest of the crew drives up from SO Central WI on our way to NW Ontario. Need to stay overnite in a cheap (~$50) motel/hotel/room, hopefully close to hwy 53. Just need a bed and TV, no bugs or rodents. Thanks in advance.

I've stayed at the Econo Lodge in Duluth. It was ok and around $60 a night. There is a decent restaurant/bar through the parking lot. Not much parking for a truck and boat. The Days Inn in Duluth is $70 and having decent parking.
Econolodge was always closer to 90$ for me. Plenty of boat parking on the other side of motel. There are a lot of mom and pop places on 53 but don't know their names. macdonald
Motel 6, Duluth. Less than $ 50.00 and next to 53. Not the nicest looking neighborhood, but I never had a problem. Best Fishes !
I always stay at the EconoLodge in Duluth at Haines Rd. No problems.
The super 8 on 53 is nice and has a quick breakfast in the morn.
The super 8 on 53 is nice and has a quick breakfast in the morn.
